Dataset Information
Source

The dataset used in this project is the German Credit Dataset, a publicly available dataset commonly used for credit risk modeling and classification tasks.

Description

The dataset contains information on 1,000 loan applicants, including both financial and demographic attributes. It is used to classify applicants into two categories:

Good credit risk
Bad credit risk
Features

Key variables include:

Age
Job
Housing status
Saving accounts
Checking accounts
Credit amount
Loan duration
Purpose of loan
Target Variable
Risk
0 → Good (low risk)
1 → Bad (high risk)
Notes
The dataset contains missing values in some financial fields (e.g., saving and checking accounts), which were handled during preprocessing.
This dataset is widely used for educational and benchmarking purposes in machine learning.
